{
  "texts": [
    "Guided by the published single-nucleus reference atlas, we designed a panel of 300 genes with 6299 padlock probes following the 3-on-4-off barcoding scheme, focusing on the major healthy cell types of the kidney, immune cells and cell states implicated in kidney disease (Supplementary Data 3).",
    "We then performed DART-FISH on tissue sections from the kidney cortex of a patient with various clinical features, including glomerulosclerosis, interstitial fibrosis, tubular atrophy, and chronic inflammation identified by a pathologist.",
    "Our gene panel correctly mapped the spatial organization of cells in different regions of the nephron, including glomeruli and cortical tubules (Fig. 4b).",
    "For instance, the transcripts NPHS2 and EMCN, which mark podocytes and glomerular capillary endothelial cells, respectively, are mainly found in the glomerular tuft of the round appearing renal corpuscles.",
    "We then compared our data with a Slide-seq dataset from a healthy individual."
  ]
}